cdd564WorkingMode.name: cdd564WorkingMode
cdd564WorkingMode.description: Configure the system's working mode. The CDM-IP can operate in any of these modes. 1. Router - Small Network Mode - The system functions as router and uses the route table to determine how to forward packets in a small network HDLC address mode. The HDLC packet uses a 1 byte HDLC address. The valid values are from 1 to 254 (0x1 - 0xFE). 2. Router - Small Network Mode - The system functions as router and uses the route table to determine how to forward packets in a large network HDLC address mode. The HDLC packet uses a 2- byte HDLC address. The valid values are from 1 to 32766 (0x1 - 0x7FFE). 3. Router - Point To Point Mode - The system functions as router but does not use HDLC addresses. 4. Router - Vipersat Mode - The system functions as router and is configured to work in a Vipersat network. *** IMPORTANT NOTE *** Changing Working mode requires the system to reboot. System configuration is saved before rebooting. Please make sure you are setting the correct value.

cdd564HDLCAddressMode.name: cdd564HDLCAddressMode
cdd564HDLCAddressMode.description: The size of HDLC address used for sending packets over satellite interface can range from 0 - 2 bytes. The satellite interface will operate in one of the following modes: 1.Small Network mode - The packet uses a 1 byte HDLC address. The valid values are from 1 to 254 (0x1 - 0xFE). 2.Large Network mode - The packet uses a 2 byte HDLC address. The valid values are from 1 to 32766 (0x1 - 0x7FFE). 3. Point To Point mode - The packet does not use a HDLC address. An HDLC address cannot have 0x00 or 0xFF in least Significant Byte. i.e., 0x400 or 0x6ff or 0x11ff are NOT valid HDLC addresses.

cdd564HDLCAddress1.name: cdd564HDLCAddress1
cdd564HDLCAddress1.description: The HDLC address #1 for the satellite interface. The valid values are: 1. Small network, 1 to 254 (0x1 - 0xFE). 2. Large network, 1 to 32766 (0x1 - 0x0x7FFE). 3. Point to point, not used. 4. EasyConnect, not used. HDLC address can not have 0x00 or 0xFF in least significant byte, i.e., 0x400 or 0x6ff or 0x11ff are NOT valid HDLC addresses. Deletion: To delete the HDLC address, set it to zero.

Point to point, not used. 4. EasyConnect, not used. HDLC address can not have 0x00 or 0xFF in least significant byte, i.e., 0x400 or 0x6ff or 0x11ff are NOT valid HDLC addresses. Deletion: To delete the HDLC address, set it to zero.

cdd564UpgradeImage.name: cdd564UpgradeImage

cdd564RestoreFactoryDefaults.name: cdd564RestoreFactoryDefaults

cdd564Reboot.name: cdd564Reboot

cdd564TotalUnicastsToEthernet.description: The total number of Unicast packets routed to the Ethernet interface.

cdd564TotalMulticastsToEthernet.name: cdd564TotalMulticastsToEthernet
cdd564TotalMulticastsToEthernet.description: The total number of Multicast packets routed to the Ethernet interface.

cdd564TotalBroadcastsToEthernet.name: cdd564TotalBroadcastsToEthernet
cdd564TotalBroadcastsToEthernet.description: The total number of Broadcast packets routed to the Ethernet interface.

cdd564TotalPacketsFromEthernet.name: cdd564TotalPacketsFromEthernet
cdd564TotalPacketsFromEthernet.description: The total number of IP packets received from the Ethernet interface.

cdd564TotalPacketsFromSatellite.name: cdd564TotalPacketsFromSatellite
cdd564TotalPacketsFromSatellite.description: The total number of IP packets received from the satellite interfaces.

cdd564TotalPacketsFromEndstation.name: cdd564TotalPacketsFromEndstation
cdd564TotalPacketsFromEndstation.description: The total number of packets received from the Endstation to be sent out one of the interfaces.

cdd564TotalPacketsToEndstation.name: cdd564TotalPacketsToEndstation
cdd564TotalPacketsToEndstation.description: The total number of packets sent to the Endstation from one of the interfaces.

cdd564IGMPPacketsReceived.name: cdd564IGMPPacketsReceived
cdd564IGMPPacketsReceived.description: The total number of IGMP packets received by the endstation.

cdd564IPOptionPacketsReceived.name: cdd564IPOptionPacketsReceived
cdd564IPOptionPacketsReceived.description: The total number of packets received with IP Options in the IP header.

cdd564TotalDroppedPackets.name: cdd564TotalDroppedPackets
cdd564TotalDroppedPackets.description: The total number of packets dropped by the router.

cdd564DroppedPacketsBadIPHeader.name: cdd564DroppedPacketsBadIPHeader
cdd564DroppedPacketsBadIPHeader.description: The total number of packets dropped by the router because of a bad checksum in the IP header.

cdd564DroppedPacketsBadBufferLength.name: cdd564DroppedPacketsBadBufferLength
cdd564DroppedPacketsBadBufferLength.description: The total number of packets dropped by the router because of a bad packet buffer length.

cdd564DroppedPacketsBadIPVersion.name: cdd564DroppedPacketsBadIPVersion
cdd564DroppedPacketsBadIPVersion.description: The total number of packets dropped by the router because of the packet is not IPv4. Note: IPv6 packets are not support by the router.

cdd564DroppedPacketsTTLExpired.name: cdd564DroppedPacketsTTLExpired
cdd564DroppedPacketsTTLExpired.description: The total number of packets dropped by the router because the TTL (time to live) in the IP header had expired (i.e. reached zero).

cdd564DroppedPacketsNoRoute.name: cdd564DroppedPacketsNoRoute
cdd564DroppedPacketsNoRoute.description: The total number of packets dropped by the router because the packet did not match any route in the route table and could not be forwarded.

cdd564DroppedPacketsNoARPEntry.name: cdd564DroppedPacketsNoARPEntry
cdd564DroppedPacketsNoARPEntry.description: The total number of packets dropped by the router because the ARP table did not have an ARP entry for the packet's next hop.

cdd564DroppedPacketsFilteredMulticast.name: cdd564DroppedPacketsFilteredMulticast
cdd564DroppedPacketsFilteredMulticast.description: The total number of multicast packets dropped by the router because the multicast address is not being forwarded.

cdd564DroppedPacketsMulticastDisableGrou.name: cdd564DroppedPacketsMulticastDisableGroup
cdd564DroppedPacketsMulticastDisableGrou.description: The total number of multicast packets dropped by the router because the multicast group is not being forwarded.

cdd564DroppedPacketsFiltered.name: cdd564DroppedPacketsFiltered
cdd564DroppedPacketsFiltered.description: The total number of packets dropped by the router for the following reasons: 1. Boot 2. Flow Descriptor 3. Unknown Reason Code 4. Flow Correlator 5. Management Path 6. Ping 7. Access Control 8. Vipersat Multicommand 9. Vipersat Unicommand 10. Codeload 11. Multicast 12. Bad Packet 13. Route 14. Bad Header Len 15. Bad Data Ptr 16. MAC Split Err 17. L3Type Err 18. Local Destination 19. ICMP Filter 20. Port Err 21. Per port route rule

cdd564DroppedPacketsRouterQueueFull.name: cdd564DroppedPacketsRouterQueueFull
cdd564DroppedPacketsRouterQueueFull.description: The total number of packets dropped by the router because the router queue is full.

cdd564IPRoutingClearCounters.name: cdd564IPRoutingClearCounters
cdd564IPRoutingClearCounters.description: This is a SET command to clear the IP routing counters.

cdd564EtherTxGoodFrames.name: cdd564EtherTxGoodFrames
cdd564EtherTxGoodFrames.description: The number of transmitted good frames from the Ethernet interface.

cdd564EtherTxMaxCollisions.name: cdd564EtherTxMaxCollisions
cdd564EtherTxMaxCollisions.description: The number of frames that were NOT transmitted because they encountered the maximum configured collisions. This counter should only increment when network is heavily saturated with traffic.

cdd564EtherTxLateCollisions.name: cdd564EtherTxLateCollisions
cdd564EtherTxLateCollisions.description: The number of frames that were NOT transmitted because they encountered collision outside the normal collision window.

cdd564EtherTxDMAUnderrun.name: cdd564EtherTxDMAUnderrun
cdd564EtherTxDMAUnderrun.description: The number of frames that were either NOT transmitted or retransmitted due to Transmit DMA underrun. Underruns occur due to lack of PCI bandwidth resulting in the internal transmit FIFO running dry during the transmission of a frame.

cdd564EtherTxLostCarrierSense.name: cdd564EtherTxLostCarrierSense
cdd564EtherTxLostCarrierSense.description: The number of frames transmitted by the device despite the fact that it detected the de-assertion of Transmit Lost Carrier Sense (CRS) during the transmission.

cdd564EtherTxDeferred.name: cdd564EtherTxDeferred
cdd564EtherTxDeferred.description: The number of frames deferred before transmission due to activity on the link.

cdd564EtherTxSingleCollisions.name: cdd564EtherTxSingleCollisions
cdd564EtherTxSingleCollisions.description: The number of transmitted frames that encountered only 1 collision.

cdd564EtherTxMultipleCollisions.name: cdd564EtherTxMultipleCollisions
cdd564EtherTxMultipleCollisions.description: The number of transmitted frames that encountered more than 1 collision.

cdd564EtherTxTotalCollisions.name: cdd564EtherTxTotalCollisions
cdd564EtherTxTotalCollisions.description: The total number of collisions that were encountered while attempting to transmit. This count includes late collisions and collisions from frames that encountered maximum collisions.

cdd564EtherTxFlowControlPauseFrames.name: cdd564EtherTxFlowControlPauseFrames
cdd564EtherTxFlowControlPauseFrames.description: The number of flow control frames transmitted by the device. This count includes both the XOFF and XON frames transmitted by the device.

cdd564EtherRxGoodFrames.name: cdd564EtherRxGoodFrames
cdd564EtherRxGoodFrames.description: The number of frames properly received from the link. It is updated only after actual reception from the link is completed and all data bytes are stored in memory.

cdd564EtherRxCRCErrorFrames.name: cdd564EtherRxCRCErrorFrames
cdd564EtherRxCRCErrorFrames.description: The number of aligned frames discarded due to CRC Errors.

cdd564EtherRxAllignmentErrors.name: cdd564EtherRxAllignmentErrors
cdd564EtherRxAllignmentErrors.description: The number of frames that are both misaligned [in other words, CRS de-asserts on a non-octet boundary] and contain a CRC error.

cdd564EtherRxResourceErrors.name: cdd564EtherRxResourceErrors
cdd564EtherRxResourceErrors.description: The number of good frames discarded due to unavailable resources.

cdd564EtherRxFIFOOverrunErrors.name: cdd564EtherRxFIFOOverrunErrors
cdd564EtherRxFIFOOverrunErrors.description: The number of frames known to be lost because the internal receive FIFO overflowed [also known as receive overrun]. This can occur if the device is unable to get necessary PCI bandwidth. If the overflow condition persists for more than one frame, the frames that follow the first can also be lost. A frame that was counted as an overrun will not be counted in other error counters like (short frames, misaligned, CRC error).

cdd564EtherRxCollisionDetectErrors.name: cdd564EtherRxCollisionDetectErrors
cdd564EtherRxCollisionDetectErrors.description: The number of frames that encountered collision during reception. This is always zero.

cdd564EtherRxShortFrames.name: cdd564EtherRxShortFrames
cdd564EtherRxShortFrames.description: The number of received frames that are shorter than the minimum frame length.

cdd564EtherRxFlowControlPauseFrames.name: cdd564EtherRxFlowControlPauseFrames
cdd564EtherRxFlowControlPauseFrames.description: The number of flow control frames received by the device. This count includes both XOFF and XON frames received.

cdd564EthernetClearCounters.name: cdd564EthernetClearCounters
cdd564EthernetClearCounters.description: Reset all ethernet transmit & receive counters.

cdd564SatelliteRxStatsTable.name: cdd564SatelliteRxStatsTable
cdd564SatelliteRxStatsTable.description: The table for Satellite interface statistics.

cdd564SatelliteRxStatsEntry.name: cdd564SatelliteRxStatsEntry
cdd564SatelliteRxStatsEntry.description: The entry for the Satellite interface statistics table.

cdd564RxStatsIndex.name: cdd564RxStatsIndex
cdd564RxStatsIndex.description: The Rx index for the satellite interface, where index can be from 1 to 4.

cdd564RxGoodFrames.name: cdd564RxGoodFrames
cdd564RxGoodFrames.description: The total number of good frames received over satellite interface.

cdd564RxHeaderBytes.name: cdd564RxHeaderBytes
cdd564RxHeaderBytes.description: The count of HDLC header bytes received over the satellite interface. HDLC header = Control + HDLC address + Flow ID + CRC

cdd564RxPayloadBytes.name: cdd564RxPayloadBytes
cdd564RxPayloadBytes.description: The count of payload bytes that were received over satellite interface, excluding any frame overhead.

cdd564RxBadHDLCAddressErrors.name: cdd564RxBadHDLCAddressErrors
cdd564RxBadHDLCAddressErrors.description: The count of received frames that did not match any of the Rx HDLC addresses.

cdd564RxPktProcCRCErrors.name: cdd564RxPktProcCRCErrors
cdd564RxPktProcCRCErrors.description: The Packet Processor CRC check is the second CRC check performed after the HDLC CRC check. It is the checksum calculated after Decryption and Payload Decompression. Failures due to 3xDES and Payload Comp are detected at this level.

cdd564RxAbortOctetErrors.name: cdd564RxAbortOctetErrors
cdd564RxAbortOctetErrors.description: The count of aborted frames and octet error frames. Aborted frame: A frame is aborted when the frame is not complete and is terminated prematurely with the Abort signal, which is 8 consecutive '1's. Octet error: A frames that was not on a byte boudary or on a multiple of 8-bit boundary.

cdd564RxOverrunErrors.name: cdd564RxOverrunErrors
cdd564RxOverrunErrors.description: The count of received frames that exceeded the maximum frame length of 2K bytes or overflowed the buffer which stores complete HDLC frames.

cdd564RxHDLCCRCErrors.name: cdd564RxHDLCCRCErrors
cdd564RxHDLCCRCErrors.description: The HDLC CRC is the first stage of the CRC check, before 3xDES and paylod Decompression. It indicates any errors due to the satellite link only.

cdd564RxInvalidFlowIDErrors.name: cdd564RxInvalidFlowIDErrors
cdd564RxInvalidFlowIDErrors.description: The number of frames received where the flow ID did not match to a valid flow descriptor.

cdd564RxSARReassembleErrors.name: cdd564RxSARReassembleErrors
cdd564RxSARReassembleErrors.description: The number of frames corresponding to a packet which had undergone segmentation and encountered an error in reassembly.

cdd564RxHeaderDecompressionErrors.name: cdd564RxHeaderDecompressionErrors
cdd564RxHeaderDecompressionErrors.description: The number of frames with a compressed IP header that encountered an error in decompressing (rebuilding) the full IP header.

cdd564RxMemoryAlignmentErrors.name: cdd564RxMemoryAlignmentErrors
cdd564RxMemoryAlignmentErrors.description: The number of frames which were incorrectly transferred (frame too small) from the Rx FPGA.

cdd564RxCRCErrors.name: cdd564RxCRCErrors
cdd564RxCRCErrors.description: The number of frames with a CRC error detected by the Rx FPGA.

cdd564SatelliteClearCounters.name: cdd564SatelliteClearCounters
cdd564SatelliteClearCounters.description: This is a SET command for clearing all the Satellite statistic counters.

cdd564RxEntry.name: cdd564RxEntry
cdd564RxEntry.description: The entry for the Demodulator table.

cdd564RxTableIndex.name: cdd564RxTableIndex
cdd564RxTableIndex.description: The index for the Rx table, where index can be from 1 to 4.

cdd564RxFEC.name: cdd564RxFEC
cdd564RxFEC.description: Rx FEC type where: 0 = Uncoded 6 = Turbo

cdd564RxCodeRate.name: cdd564RxCodeRate
cdd564RxCodeRate.description: Rx code rate, where 4 = Rate 3/4 5 = Rate 7/8 6 = Rate 0.95 7 = Rate 1/1 (Uncoded)

cdd564RxDataRate.name: cdd564RxDataRate
cdd564RxDataRate.description: Rx data rate in bps (Varies based on chart below.) Units = bps Resolution = 1 bps FEC Type Modulation Code Rate Data Rate High Rate -------- ----------- ---------- --------------------- --------- Turbo QPSK Rate 3/4 16.0 Kbps to 4.5 Mbps N/A Turbo QPSK Rate 7/8 16.0 Kbps to 5.0 Mbps 5.25 Mbps Turbo QPSK Rate 0.95 16.0 Kbps to 5.0 Mbps 5.667 Mbps Turbo 8-PSK Rate 3/4 16.0 Kbps to 5.0 Mbps 6.75 Mbps Turbo 8-PSK Rate 7/8 16.0 Kbps to 5.0 Mbps 7.875 Mbps Turbo 8-PSK Rate 0.95 16.0 Kbps to 5.0 Mbps 8.5 Mbps Turbo 16-QAM Rate 3/4 16.0 Kbps to 5.0 Mbps 9.0 Mbps Turbo 16-QAM Rate 7/8 16.8 Kbps to 5.0 Mbps 9.98 Mbps

cdd564RxFrequency.name: cdd564RxFrequency
cdd564RxFrequency.description: Rx frequency for L-Band and IF-Band modes. L-Band is 950 MHz to 1950 MHz. IF-Band is 50 MHz to 90 MHz and 100 MHz to 180 MHz. Units = Hz. Resolution = 100 Hz.

cdd564RxAcquisitionSweepWidth.name: cdd564RxAcquisitionSweepWidth
cdd564RxAcquisitionSweepWidth.description: Rx +/- acquisition sweep range of demodulator, in KHz, ranging from: +/- 1 to +/- 32 KHz (rates < 625 ksym/second) or +/- 1 to 200 KHz (rates >= 625 ksym/second)

cdd564RxDescrambling.name: cdd564RxDescrambling
cdd564RxDescrambling.description: Rx descrambler state, where: 0 = Off 1 = On (default descrambler type) 2 = On - IESS-315 (Turbo only)

cdd564RxBufferSize.name: cdd564RxBufferSize
cdd564RxBufferSize.description: Rx buffer size, where: 0 = Buffer disabled (Clock mode = Rx satellite)

cdd546RxSpectrumInversion.name: cdd546RxSpectrumInversion
cdd546RxSpectrumInversion.description: Rx spectrum inversion, where: 0 = Normal 1 = Rx spectrum inverted

cdd564RxDataInversion.name: cdd564RxDataInversion
cdd564RxDataInversion.description: Invert receive data, where: 0 = Normal 1 = Inverted

cdd564RxEbNoAlarmPoint.name: cdd564RxEbNoAlarmPoint
cdd564RxEbNoAlarmPoint.description: Rx Eb/No alarm point in 0.1 dB, with a range between 0.1 dB and 16 dB. Units = 0.1 dB Resolution = 0.1 dB

cdd564RxRecenterBuffer.name: cdd564RxRecenterBuffer
cdd564RxRecenterBuffer.description: This is a SET command that recenters the receive Plesiochronous/Doppler buffer.

cdd564RxSymbolRate.name: cdd564RxSymbolRate
cdd564RxSymbolRate.description: Rx symbol rate in symbols per second (sym) Units = sym Resolution = 1 sym

cdd564AGCAlarmMask.name: cdd564AGCAlarmMask
cdd564AGCAlarmMask.description: Rx AGC alarm mask, where: 0 = Unmasked 1 = Masked

cdd564EbNoAlarmMask.name: cdd564EbNoAlarmMask
cdd564EbNoAlarmMask.description: Eb/No alarm mask, where: 0 = Unmasked 1 = Masked

cdd564LNBAlarmMask.name: cdd564LNBAlarmMask
cdd564LNBAlarmMask.description: LNB alarm mask, where: 0 = Unmasked 1 = Masked

cdd564ReferenceFrequency.name: cdd564ReferenceFrequency
cdd564ReferenceFrequency.description: External reference frequency, where: 0 = Internal 10 MHz

cdd564InternalReferenceAdjust.name: cdd564InternalReferenceAdjust
cdd564InternalReferenceAdjust.description: Internal Reference Adjust, from -999 to +999. Units = KHz

cdd564LNBEntry.name: cdd564LNBEntry
cdd564LNBEntry.description: The entry for the LNBs table.

cdd564LNBDCPower.name: cdd564LNBDCPower
cdd564LNBDCPower.description: LNB power control, where: 0 = Off 1 = On, 13V LNB voltage 2 = On, 18V LNB voltage 3 = On, 24V LNB voltage

cdd564LNB10MHzReference.name: cdd564LNB10MHzReference
cdd564LNB10MHzReference.description: LNB 10MHz frequency reference, where: 0 = Disable LNB 10MHz reference 1 = Enable LNB 10MHz reference

cdm564LLNBLowCurrentLimit.name: cdm564LLNBLowCurrentLimit
cdm564LLNBLowCurrentLimit.description: LNB lower alarm limit for current, between 10 and 400 mA.

cdd564LNBHighCurrentLimit.name: cdd564LNBHighCurrentLimit
cdd564LNBHighCurrentLimit.description: LNB upper alarm limit for current, between 50 and 600 mA.

cdd564LNBLOFrequency.name: cdd564LNBLOFrequency
cdd564LNBLOFrequency.description: LNB receieve LO frequency, in the range of 3000 to 65000 MHz. Setting a 0 disables the feature. Terminal Frequency = LNB_LO +/- Rx_Frequency (depending on High/Low Mix)

cdd564LNBLOMix.name: cdd564LNBLOMix
cdd564LNBLOMix.description: LO frequency mix, where: 0 = Low-side mix 1 = High-side mix

cdd564SoftwareRevision.name: cdd564SoftwareRevision
cdd564SoftwareRevision.description: Unit returns the value of the internal software revision installed in the unit, in the form of x.x.x.

cdd564UnitAlarm.name: cdd564UnitAlarm
cdd564UnitAlarm.description: Modem Unit Faults: Value Description of unit fault 0 No faults 1 +5 Volt power supply 2 +12 Volt power supply 3 -5 Volt power supply 4 +23 Volt power supply 5 -12 Volt power supply 6 Rx 1st LO synthesize lock 7 Rx 2nd LO synthesize lock 8 Ref PLL lock 9 EEPROM checksum error

cdd564Temperature.name: cdd564Temperature
cdd564Temperature.description: Unit returns the value of the internal temperature, in degrees Celsius.

cdd564RxMonitorEntry.name: cdd564RxMonitorEntry
cdd564RxMonitorEntry.description: The entry for the demoduator monitor table.

cdd564RxMonitorIndex.name: cdd564RxMonitorIndex
cdd564RxMonitorIndex.description: The index for the demodulator monitor table.

cdd564RxAlarm.name: cdd564RxAlarm
cdd564RxAlarm.description: Modem RX Traffic Faults Value Description of status parameter 0 Rx Traffic OK 1 Demodulator unlocked 3 AGC Alarm - signal out of range 10 Buffer underflow 11 Buffer overflow 13 Eb/No alarm 15 AIS detected on incoming data

cdd564RxEbNo.name: cdd564RxEbNo
cdd564RxEbNo.description: Unit returns the value of Eb/No, between 0 and 16 db. Units = 0.1 dB Resolution 0.1 dB Returns 999 if demod is unlocked. For values greater than 16 dB, the reply will be 160.

cdd564RxSignalLevel.name: cdd564RxSignalLevel
cdd564RxSignalLevel.description: Unit returns the value of the Rx signal level, in dBm, between -20 and -99 dBm, Returns -100 if signal is less than -99dBm. Returns -19 if signal is greater than -20dBm.

cdd564RxFreqOffset.name: cdd564RxFreqOffset
cdd564RxFreqOffset.description: Unit returns the value of the measured frequency offset of the carrier being demodulated in Hz. Units = Hz. Resolution 100 Hz. Range = -200,000 Hz to 0 Hz and 0 Hz to 200,000 Hz.

cddRxBERMultiplier.name: cddRxBERMultiplier
cddRxBERMultiplier.description: Estimated corrected BER. The BER is calculated by multiplying the Multiplier by 10E-10. Calculuation: RxBER = (Multiplier) * 0.0000000001 Returns 2147483647 (max int) if demod is unlocked.

cdd564LNBMonitorEntry.name: cdd564LNBMonitorEntry
cdd564LNBMonitorEntry.description: The entry for the LNBs monitoring table.

cdd564LNBMonitorIndex.name: cdd564LNBMonitorIndex
cdd564LNBMonitorIndex.description: The index for the LNBs monitoring table.

cdd564LNBAlarm.name: cdd564LNBAlarm
cdd564LNBAlarm.description: LNB alarms Value Description of status parameter 0 No LNB faults 7 LNB current 9 LNB voltage

cdd564LNBCurrent.name: cdd564LNBCurrent
cdd564LNBCurrent.description: Indicates the value of the LNB current, between 0 and 999 mA.

cdd564LNBVoltage.name: cdd564LNBVoltage
cdd564LNBVoltage.description: Indicates the value of the LNB voltage, between 0 and 30 volts. Units = 0.1 volts If not available, response is 0.

cdd564LNBTerminalRxFreq.name: cdd564LNBTerminalRxFreq
cdd564LNBTerminalRxFreq.description: Terminal Rx frequency = LNB LO +/- Rx_Frequency (depending on LO mix) Units = 100 Hz Resolution = 100 Hz Returns 0 if LNB_LO is zero.

cdd564StoredEventsTable.name: cdd564StoredEventsTable
cdd564StoredEventsTable.description: The table of stored events for all four demods.

cdd564StoredEventsEntry.name: cdd564StoredEventsEntry
cdd564StoredEventsEntry.description: The entry for stored events table for all 4 demods.

cdd564EventDemod.name: cdd564EventDemod
cdd564EventDemod.description: The demodulator index for which event log is being returned.

cdd564EventIndex.name: cdd564EventIndex
cdd564EventIndex.description: The index for a demod's stored events table.

cdd564EventDescription.name: cdd564EventDescription
cdd564EventDescription.description: Event description string with the following format seprated by commas: 1. Date in form dd/mm/yy, where: dd = day of the month (01 to 31) mm = month (01 to 12) yy = year (00 to 99) 2. Time in form hh:mm:ss, where: hh = hours (00 to 23) mm = minutes (00 to 59) ss = seconds (00 to 59) 3. Event Type in form xxxxx, where xxxxx is Clear = fault cleared Fault = fault occurred Info = information 4. Texual Description of Event

cdd564ClearAllStoredEvents.name: cdd564ClearAllStoredEvents
cdd564ClearAllStoredEvents.description: This is a SET command to clear the event log for one of the four demods (1 - 4).

cdd564StoredStatisticsTable.description: The table of stored statistics for all four demods.

cdd564StoredStatisticsEntry.description: The entry for stored statistics table for all four demods.

cdd564StatisticDemod.name: cdd564StatisticDemod
cdd564StatisticDemod.description: The demod index for which statistics table is being returned.

cdd564StatisticIndex.name: cdd564StatisticIndex
cdd564StatisticIndex.description: The index in one of the four demod's stored statistics table.

cdd564StatisticDate.name: cdd564StatisticDate
cdd564StatisticDate.description: The date of the statistic in the form dd/mm/yy, where: dd = day of the month (01 to 31) mm = month (01 to 12) yy = year (00 to 99)

cdd564StatisticTime.description: The time of the statistic in the form hh:mm:ss, indicating the time from midnight, where: hh = hours (00 to 23) mm = minutes (00 to 59) ss = seconds (00 to 59)

cdd564StatisticAvgEbNo.description: Minimum Eb/No during sample period. Units = 0.1 dB. Returns 999 if demod was unlocked during sample period.

cdd564StatisticMinEbNo.name: cdd564StatisticMinEbNo
cdd564StatisticMinEbNo.description: Minimum Eb/No during sample period. Units = 0.1 dB. Returns 999 if demod was unlocked during sample period.

cdd564StoredStatisticsConfigTable.name: cdd564StoredStatisticsConfigTable
cdd564StoredStatisticsConfigTable.description: The configuration for the stored statistics (per Demod).

cdd564StoredStatisticsConfigEntry.name: cdd564StoredStatisticsConfigEntry
cdd564StoredStatisticsConfigEntry.description: The entry for the stored statistics configuration table.

cdd564StatisticsSampleInterval.name: cdd564StatisticsSampleInterval
cdd564StatisticsSampleInterval.description: Used to set the sample interval for the statistics logging function, where the enumerated lists goes from 0 to 9 in 10 minute steps. Setting 0 disables the statistics logging function.

cdd564ClearAllStoredStatistics.name: cdd564ClearAllStoredStatistics
cdd564ClearAllStoredStatistics.description: This is a SET command to clear the statistics log for one of the four demods (1 - 4).

cdd564RTCDate.name: cdd564RTCDate
cdd564RTCDate.description: A date in the form dd/mm/yy, where dd = day of the month (01 to 31) mm = month (01 to 12) yy = year (00 to 99)

cdd564RTCTime.name: cdd564RTCTime
cdd564RTCTime.description: A time in the form hh:mm:ss, indicating the time from midnight, where: hh = hours (00 to 23) mm = minutes (00 to 59) ss = seconds (00 to 59)

cdd564CircuitIDEntry.description: The entry for the circuit ID table.
